<a href="#0" id="0">We initially allow each English word type to map to any sequence of Pinyin, up to length 7, with uniform probability.</a>
<a href="#1" id="1">To improve the accuracy of word-based EM alignment, we use the phoneme based model to decode each English word in the training data to Pinyin.</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">The word-based model can only decode 29 of the 65 test utterances, because wFST E fails if an utterance contains a new English word type, previously unseen in training.</a>
